<!-- --><p>but the usual thing i do for cohost is use one of the generic family names (which you should always have as the last in your font list anyway), in which case the browser will just pick a relevant default: <!-- --><span style="font-family:serif">serif<!-- --></span>, <!-- --><span style="font-family:sans-serif">sans-serif<!-- --></span>, <!-- --><span style="font-family:monospace">monospace<!-- --></span> are the most reliable; <!-- --><span style="font-family:cursive">cursive<!-- --></span> and <!-- --><span style="font-family:fantasy">fantasy<!-- --></span> are possibly more hit-or-miss (i get Comic Neue and Impact, what?); and i have never seen anyone use <!-- --><span style="font-family:system-ui">system-ui<!-- --></span>, <!-- --><span style="font-family:ui-serif">ui-serif<!-- --></span>, <!-- --><span style="font-family:ui-sans-serif">ui-sans-serif<!-- --></span>, <!-- --><span style="font-family:ui-monospace">ui-monospace<!-- --></span>, <!-- --><span style="font-family:ui-rounded">ui-rounded<!-- --></span>, <!-- --><span style="font-family:emoji">emoji<!-- --></span>, <!-- --><span style="font-family:math">math<!-- --></span>, or <!-- --><span style="font-family:fangsong">fangsong<!-- --></span>.<!-- --></p>
